, admirers, and scholars the first of three volumes and presents Mark Twain's authentic and unsuppressed voice, brimming with humor, ideas, and opinions, and speaking clearly from the grave as he intended. Editors: Harriet E. Smith, Benjamin Griffin, Victor Fischer, Michael B. Frank, Sharon K. Goetz, Leslie Myrick  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAuthors, AmericanxBiographyx19th century. 0aAuthors, Americany19th centuryvBiography. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  a19th century.  a20th century authors.  aadventures.  aamerican authors.  aamerican lit.  aamerican south.  aamerican.  aautobiography.  aclassics.  acoming of age.  acritic.  aengaging.  afamous authors.  afree thoughts.  ahistorical.  ahumorist.  alife journey.  alife lessons.  alife story.  aliterary criticism.  aliterary icon.  aliterary.  alively.  amark twain.  amemoir.  anonfiction.  aopinionated.  apage turner.  apublic figure.  astudents and teachers.  atwain scholars.  auncensored.1 aFischer, Victor, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFrank, Michael Barry, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGriffin, Benjamin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSmith, Harriet E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094699640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520946996423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520946996/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles